  "prompt": "How long does diarrhea last?",
  "response": "The duration of diarrhea can vary depending on its cause. Acute diarrhea, which is often caused by infections (viral, bacterial, or parasitic), usually lasts from a few days up to a week. It typically resolves on its own without the need for medical treatment.\n\nChronic diarrhea, on the other hand, persists for more than four weeks and may be associated with underlying medical conditions such as inflammatory bowel disease, irritable bowel syndrome, or malabsorption disorders. \n\nIf diarrhea lasts more than two days for adults or 24 hours for children, or if there are severe symptoms (like dehydration, high fever, or blood in the stool), it's important to seek medical attention. Always consult a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate treatment if you have concerns.",
